definition: X is the 24th letter of the English alphabet

senses.definition: ' In algebra, x is used as a symbol to represent an unknown value.
example: The head of the drug ring in Australia is Mr X[j4]he's known to police as a prominent Sydney businessman

definition: for Christ~ mas in informal written English

senses.definition: ' An x-ray is a photograph of the inside of part of the human body taken by x-rays. Doctors use these to help them diagnose a patient's condition or disease.
example: They are used to take photographs of the inside of things, such as the human body and luggage at airports
They took an x-ray just to be sure my arm wasn't broken
